If you want the email body in HTML format with a professional table, create an HTML file and send it using mailx.

Create HTML Report

HTML_REPORT="/tmp/mstrbak_report.html"

cat > "$HTML_REPORT" <<EOF
<html>
<head>
<style>
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}
table {
    border-collapse: collapse;
    width: 80%;
}
th {
    background-color: #1F4E78;
    color: white;
    padding: 8px;
    text-align: left;
}
td {
    border: 1px solid #cccccc;
    padding: 8px;
}
.success {
    color: green;
    font-weight: bold;
}
.failed {
    color: red;
    font-weight: bold;
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<h2>MicroStrategy Backup Execution Summary</h2>

<table>
<tr>
<th>Item</th>
<th>Value</th>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Hostname</td>
<td>$HOSTNAME</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Project Source Name</td>
<td>$PROJECT_SOURCE</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Backup Status</td>
<td class="success">$BACKUP_STATUS</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Renamed Archive File</td>
<td>$ARCHIVE_NAME</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Backup File</td>
<td>$BACKUP_FILE</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>S3 Upload Status</td>
<td class="success">$S3_UPLOAD_STATUS</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>S3 Bucket File</td>
<td>$S3_FILE</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Log File</td>
<td>$LOG_FILE</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Execution Time</td>
<td>$(date)</td>
</tr>

</table>

<br>

<p>
Regards,<br>
MicroStrategy Backup Automation
</p>

</body>
</html>

EOF

Send HTML Email

Using mailx:

(
echo "To: $TEAM_DL"
echo "Subject: [MSTRBak] Backup Status - $PROJECT_SOURCE - $BACKUP_STATUS"
echo "MIME-Version: 1.0"
echo "Content-Type: text/html"
echo
cat "$HTML_REPORT"
) | sendmail -t

Or:

mailx \
-a "MIME-Version: 1.0" \
-a "Content-Type: text/html" \
-s "[MSTRBak] Backup Status - $PROJECT_SOURCE - $BACKUP_STATUS" \
"$TEAM_DL" < "$HTML_REPORT"

Attach Log File

mailx \
-a "$LOG_FILE" \
-a "MIME-Version: 1.0" \
-a "Content-Type: text/html" \
-s "[MSTRBak] Backup Status - $PROJECT_SOURCE - $BACKUP_STATUS" \
"$TEAM_DL" < "$HTML_REPORT"

Failure Status Coloring

Before generating HTML:

if [ "$BACKUP_STATUS" = "SUCCESS" ]; then
    STATUS_CLASS="success"
else
    STATUS_CLASS="failed"
fi

Then use:

<td class="$STATUS_CLASS">$BACKUP_STATUS</td>

This will show:

🟢 Green for SUCCESS

🔴 Red for FAILED


and provide a professional HTML email summary for your MicroStrategy backup automation.
